patch.description:
Partially update a brand — send ONLY the fields you want to change.

━━━  Flutter: used in BrandDetailScreen edit button  ━━━
```dart
// Only send changed fields — no need to re-send everything
await api.patch('/api/brands/$brandId', data: {'name': newName});
await api.patch('/api/brands/$brandId', data: {'logo': newLogoUrl});
await api.patch('/api/brands/$brandId', data: {
  'targetAudience': 'Gen Z',
  'category': 'Fashion',
});
```

Field mapping (Flutter camelCase → API snake_case):
  targetAudience  → target_audience
  All others are identical.

get.description:
Bulk fetch — returns everything the app needs in ONE call.

━━━  Flutter: call on login / app resume  ━━━
```dart
final res = await dio.get('/api/app-data');
final brands   = (res.data['brands'] as List).map(Brand.fromJson).toList();
final products = (res.data['products'] as List).map(Product.fromJson).toList();
final user     = UserModel.fromJson(res.data['user']);
final stats    = res.data['stats'];
```
